The remaining half of the students are under 16 years old, and one-half of the students under 16 are male. In total, how many female students are enrolled at this school?

ost_step.1: Calculate the number of students who are older than 16. This is (1/2) * 6525618 = 3262809 students.
ost_step.2: Determine the number of males above age 16 which equals (1/4)*3262809 = 815702 students.
ost_step.3: Subtracting those from Step 2 we get females aged >16 as follows : 3262809-(815702)=2447107 people.
ost_step.4: Find out that all younger pupils add up for another (1/2)*6525618=3262809 peoples. And calculate their mals as followings:(1/2)×(3262809)(1/2)=815702 people. That means finding women below age 16 yields us: 3262809–815702=2447017 girls.
ost_step.5: Summing them together gets our needed result; so adding answers gotten on Steps 3 & 4 ,we find Female Students at Brook Hills High School being equal to  2447107+2447017=4894124.
